nested if task
Check if a number is positive → then check if it is even or odd.
Check if student passed all subjects → then check if eligible for distinction (average ≥ 75).
Check if age ≥ 18 → then check if user has driving license.
Check if login username is correct → then check if password is correct.
Check if number is divisible by 5 → then check if also divisible by 10.
Check if year is divisible by 4 → then check leap year conditions (divisible by 100 and 400).
Check if salary > 30,000 → then check if experience > 5 years for bonus.
Check if number is three-digit → then check if it is palindrome.
Check if character is alphabet → then check if it is uppercase or lowercase.
Check if triangle sides are valid → then check if it is equilateral / isosceles.
Check if account balance > 0 → then check if withdrawal amount ≤ balance.
Check if temperature > 0 → then check if less than 20 (Cold category).
Check if marks ≥ 35 → then check if marks ≥ 90 (Topper).
Check if number > 1 → then check if prime.
Check if password length ≥ 8 → then check if it contains a digit.
Check if input is digit → then check if it is even digit.
Check if employee department is "IT" → then check if performance rating ≥ 4.
Check if purchase amount > 1000 → then check if customer is premium member.
Check if number is divisible by 2 → then check if divisible by 4.
Check if student attendance ≥ 75% → then check if marks ≥ 50 for exam eligibility.
